trans-unit.source: Encapsulates basic validation rules that indicate whether a piece of custom data is considered personalizable in either <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope"></xref> scope.

trans-unit.source: A PersonalizationDictionary instance is a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry> objects, which consist of a personalization scope and an object value.
trans-unit.target: En PersonalizationDictionary-instans är en samling <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry>objekt, som består av en anpassningsläge och ett Objektvärde.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry>

trans-unit.source: These entries are assigned a key in the PersonalizationDictionary object.
trans-unit.target: De här posterna har tilldelats en nyckel i PersonalizationDictionary-objektet.

trans-unit.source: A good practice is to add all properties to the dictionary using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> method, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: Är en bra idé att lägga till alla egenskaper i en ordlista med hjälp av den <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>metoden oavsett omfånget för sidan.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework saves the information in the appropriate way; for example, shared data is saved when the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: .NET Framework sparar informationen på lämpligt sätt. till exempel delade data sparas när sidan är i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: However, shared properties are not saved when a Web Parts value is being saved, the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added with the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: Dock delade egenskaper sparas inte när ett värde för webbdelar sparas, sidan finns i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång, och <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen har lagts till med sidan i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: When a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, you can add name and state information that is associated with either <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: När en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>kontrollen är i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång, du kan lägga till information om namn och tillstånd som associeras med antingen <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång eller <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager>

trans-unit.source: In <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, you can add name and state information associated only with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: I <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång, du kan lägga till information om namn och tillstånd som associeras med endast <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: It is a good practice, however, to add all properties to the dictionary using <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> including properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: Det är dock en bra idé att lägga till alla egenskaper i en ordlista med hjälp av <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>inklusive egenskaper med <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>eller <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång, oavsett omfånget för sidan.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A>

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework only saves the properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope when appropriate.
trans-unit.target: .NET Framework sparar endast egenskaper med <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång när det är lämpligt.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>

trans-unit.source: In other words, shared properties are not saved when a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control that was initially added in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope.
trans-unit.target: Delas med andra ord egenskaper sparas inte när en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontroll som ursprungligen lades till i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång sparas senare medan sidan <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång.</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: In an opposite scenario, if a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added to the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, and the control is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> scope, custom shared property values are saved (along with custom user-scoped properties).
trans-unit.target: I ett motsatt scenario om en <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>kontrollen har lagts till i sidan i <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång och kontrollen sparas senare medan sidan <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope>omfång, anpassade delade egenskapsvärden sparas (tillsammans med egna användarspecifika egenskaper).</xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope> </xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart>

trans-unit.source: For details on personalization data and how shared and user-scoped properties are affected by the personalization scope of the page, see the [Web Parts Personalization Overview](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) topic.
trans-unit.target: Information om anpassningsdata och hur delade och användarspecifika egenskaper som påverkas av anpassningsläge för sidan, finns det [översikt över webbserver delar anpassning](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md) avsnittet.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Add%2A> method checks several details to ensure the validity of `value` and `key` before attempting to add them to the personalization dictionary.
